{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH7EmYhg8zQmDJ8DN3RL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. Tests pass.\n\n**The bug:** `getUsers` cached results under the key `users:${opts.team}`, which ignored the `includeArchived` flag. When something called `getUsers({ team, includeArchived: true })`, its archived-inclusive list got cached under the plain team key. The people picker — which calls with `includeArchived: false` — then read that same cache entry and showed archived users. The 60s TTL is why refreshing \"after a minute\" clears it: the poisoned entry expires.\n\n**The fix** (`src/userService.js:10`) folds `includeArchived` into the cache key, so archived-inclusive and active-only results are stored separately and never leak into each other.\n\nThere's no test covering `userService.js` (the existing suite only tests the cache), so this behavior wasn't caught. Want me to add a regression test asserting that an `includeArchived: true` call doesn't poison a subsequent `includeArchived: false` call?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":316,"cache_read_input_tokens":23175,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":316},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d925051-28dd-4ddb-9592-369773062b00","uuid":"eae8a322-3f99-4077-a2af-cca413132e23","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:37:53.370Z","request_id":"req_011CdH7Ejrkjf5X7bb5HvFVc"}
